SonicDE SlackBuild for Slackware
================================

Builds SonicDE packages for Slackware-current by replacing selected KDE/Plasma
packages. Install Slackware's KDE set first; SonicDE still uses many KDE,
Plasma, Frameworks, Gear, Qt6, and integration packages from Slackware.

Quick start
-----------
Install Slackware KDE first:

  slackpkg install kde

Make sure the main Slackware `polkit` package is installed too. The agents are
not enough; `sonic-polkit` needs `polkit-gobject-1.pc` from the main `polkit`
package:

  slackpkg install polkit

Verify it with:

  pkg-config --exists polkit-gobject-1 && echo OK

Before downloading sources, check for newer public SonicDE tags:

  cd sonicde
  ./sonicde_check_tags.sh

If it shows UPDATE entries, refresh `source-versions` first. For new packages,
you may also need to update `modules/sonic`, `package-renames`, `pkgsrc/*`, and
`slack-desc/*`.

Then download SonicDE sources, build, and install:

  cd sonicde
  ./sonicde_checkout.sh -c -f sonic
  TMP=/tmp/sonicde-build SLACK_KDE_BUILD_DIR=/tmp/sonicde-packages UPGRADE=yes SKIPBUILT=no EXITFAIL=yes ./sonicde.SlackBuild sonic

Reboot or restart the graphical session after installation.

KDE package replacement
-----------------------
Do not remove Slackware's KDE packages before building/installing SonicDE.
Install Slackware's KDE set first, then build SonicDE with `UPGRADE=yes`.

For packages listed in `sonicde/package-renames`, the SlackBuild replaces the
installed Slackware package automatically. For example, if `plasma-workspace` is
installed and SonicDE builds `sonic-workspace`, the install step uses Slackware's
`upgradepkg old%new` syntax:

  upgradepkg --install-new --reinstall plasma-workspace%sonic-workspace-...

This removes the replaced KDE/Plasma package and installs the SonicDE package in
one step. If the original KDE package is not installed, the SonicDE package is
installed normally.

Do not remove the whole KDE set after installing SonicDE. SonicDE still depends
on many Qt6, Frameworks, Plasma, Gear, and integration packages from Slackware
that are not replaced by this SlackBuild.

After installation, check for leftover replaced KDE packages with:

  cd sonicde
  ./sonicde_remove_replaced.sh -n

The dry run should report replaced packages as not installed. If it reports a
replaced KDE/Plasma package still installed, inspect it before removing; it may
indicate an incomplete SonicDE install or a package that was reinstalled later.

Avoid running `slackpkg install kde` after SonicDE is installed, because it may
install KDE packages that SonicDE intentionally replaced. For Slackware-current
updates, update Slackware first, then rebuild/reinstall the SonicDE replacements
as needed.

Useful checks
-------------
Show packages that will be built:

  cd sonicde
  PRECHECK=yes GRACETME=0 PRINT_PACKAGE_NAME=1 ./sonicde.SlackBuild sonic

Check installed SonicDE packages:

  ls /var/log/packages/sonic-* | sort

Check that replaced KDE/Plasma packages are gone:

  cd sonicde
  ./sonicde_remove_replaced.sh -n

That command should report the replaced KDE/Plasma packages as not installed.

